          "author": {
            "login": "ConcaveTrillion"
          },
          "body": "Discovered while adding the `source` provenance field (commit e0fb16d).\n\nTwo divergences from pd-ocr-labeler-spa `specs/20-glyph-annotations.md` remain unresolved:\n\n1. **LigatureKind** — upstream values are lowercase with a different member set (has FF/LONG_S_S/LONG_S_I/SP/QU, lacks OE/AE, names LONG_S_T); the SPA spec wants UPPERCASE values, drops/adds members, and renames to LONG_ST. Changing enum values is a wire-format break for #41-era persisted snapshots — needs a migration plan.\n2. **dataclass vs Pydantic** — the upstream model is a `@dataclass`; the SPA spec writes it as a Pydantic `BaseModel`. Decide whether the SPA adapts or upstream converts.\n\nBlocks full completion of the pd-ocr-labeler-spa glyph epic (#267-#270).",
          "closedAt": "2026-05-22T16:11:01Z",
          "comments": {
            "nodes": []
          },
          "createdAt": "2026-05-22T14:47:52Z",
